The method returns a boolean value indicating whether the `word` exists in the `board`.
If the `word` exists in the `board`, the method returns `true`.
If the `word` does not exist in the `board`, the method returns `false`.
The same letter cell in the `board` cannot be used more than once to construct the `word`.
The `word` can be constructed from letters of sequentially adjacent cells, where adjacent cells are horizontally or vertically neighboring.
